        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "[codex] Forward opt-in run context headers",
        "body": "Closes #93436.\n\n## Summary\n\n- Add `compat.requestContextHeaders` for OpenAI-compatible models/providers so operators can map `runId`, `messageChannel`, and `runKind` to provider request header names.\n- Attach embedded run context to model stream calls and have OpenAI-compatible transports emit those headers only when the mapping is configured.\n- Preserve provider-level defaults, model-level overrides, catalog normalization, config schema/help metadata, and caller-header precedence.\n\n## Behavior addressed\n\nModel requests can now forward OpenClaw run context to an OpenAI-compatible proxy for attribution without sending anything by default. The opt-in mapping supports `runId`, `messageChannel`, and `runKind` (`message`, `heartbeat`, or `cron`).\n\n## Real environment tested\n\nLocal OpenClaw checkout on branch `openmeta/93436-run-context-headers`, commit `61a422b2b65d511782fc44f2aa1e7715640ad28b`.\n\n## Exact steps or command run after this patch\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/openai-transport-stream.test.ts src/config/zod-schema.models.test.ts packages/model-catalog-core/src/model-catalog-normalize.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.model-run-context.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/model.inline-provider.test.ts src/agents/sessions/model-registry.test.ts src/agents/model-compat.test.ts\nnode scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p tsconfig.core.json --incremental false\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/llm/providers/openai-completions.test.ts src/llm/providers/openai-responses-shared.test.ts src/llm/providers/openai-compatible-auth.test.ts src/agents/openai-completions-compat.test.ts\n```\n\n## Evidence after fix\n\n- Targeted Vitest run passed: 4 shards, 7 files, 359 tests.\n- Core typecheck completed with exit code 0.\n- Provider-focused Vitest run passed: 2 shards, 4 files, 63 tests.\n\n## Observed result after fix\n\n- `buildOpenAIClientHeaders` emits run context headers when `compat.requestContextHeaders` maps a field to a header name.\n- Without an explicit mapping, no `x-openclaw-*` run context headers are emitted.\n- Static provider/model headers are overridden by dynamic run context headers, while explicit caller/turn headers still win.\n- Provider-level request context mappings merge with model-level mappings in both the session registry and embedded inline provider path.\n\n## What was not tested\n\n- I did not send a live request through an external attribution proxy; coverage is local unit/type validation of header construction and run-context propagation.\n",
